properties.abstract: The Schweizerweg (Swiss trail) leads directly up to Schesaplana from Schesaplanahütte. It goes through a rocky escarpment that, viewed from afar, seems to be insurmountable. Actually, it is surprisingly easy to hike up and down this passage. In the upper part of the ascent you go along a number of ledges which are of geological interest. The whole tour is ideal for alpine hiking rookies.
properties.subtitle: Teh Schweizerweg
properties.title: From Schesaplanahütte

sac_photos.title: On the ledges leading up the last stretch to Schesaplana
The ascent is on the south cliffs of the Schesaplana range, slightly left of the centre of the photo.

segments.description: From Schesaplanahütte ascend steeply on a blue-white marked trail to the rocky escarpment. Following the fall line and past schrofen steps hike up to P. 2427. There the trail turns eastward to traverse the huge talus on schist ledges. From Schesaplanasattel go northward directly to the summit.
segments.title: Schesaplanahütte - Schweizerweg - Schesaplana

segments.description: Descend 40 metres of vertical height, then turn eastward to reach Totalp, overcoming a steep step. Continue to descend to Gamsluggen, where some chains secure the way down to Prättigauer Höhenweg, which you follow to Schesaplanahütte.
segments.title: Schesaplana - Gamsluggen – Schesaplanahütte
